oai_dc:dc.dc:title: Movements on the Federal Front
oai_dc:dc.dc:creator: Jennings, Jerry
oai_dc:dc.dc:description: Tremors are being felt from Washington as thesluggish machinery of the USDI begins to grind outthe final version of the "Injurious Wildlife Proposal"An unofficial, tentative list of "low risk" birds hasbeen obtained by the pet industry as a result of theAd Hoc Committee negotiations between the USDIand PIJAC*. Though the list is a step forward fromthe original proposal's list of four birds it is stillmore noteworthy for what it restricts than whatit allows.
